items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall
Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 
Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.
Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 
The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information, contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

**CASTING CALL - Featured Extras and Background**

**Title:** CrimeCast (Episode 01A)

**Genre:** Dark Comedy, Crime Mystery, Episodic 

**Logline:** Emotionally unstable True Crime podcast host wants answers, but has to decide which is more important: her friends' and family's safety or the truth of what happened to her dead best friend.

**Roles:**

**Featured Extras and Background:**

**We are seeking a diverse group of individuals to fill approximately 10 featured extra and background roles.**

**Contact info: If you are interested and available, please send a selfie or headshot along with your height to **[crimecast22@gmail.com](mailto:crimecast22@gmail.com) **and** [phyllisramie@gmail.com](mailto:phyllisramie@gmail.com)

**Director:** Phyllis Ramie Groves

**Director of Photography:** Xavier Leonard

**Production Type:** Student Film (Prod 3)

**Compensation:** Unpaid. Food, Footage, and Credit.

**Shooting Date and Location:** October 15th in Castle Rock, CO. Carpooling from CCA may be available.

CASTING CALL: FOSSILIZED - A CU DENVER STUNDENT FILM  

We are desperately looking for child actors for Fossilized, a senior thesis student film in the CU Denver FiTV program. This is unpaid, and will instead be a copy/credit/meal basis.

If interested, please reach out to -

Rowan Harper (Casting Director) at rowan.harper@ucdenver.edu

Arthur Rice (Producer) at arthur.rice@ucdenver.edu

items.text:
Hey everyone my name is Manraj Heer I‚Äôm the producer for our student short film at Vancouver Film School. The film is called ‚ÄúBeginnings‚Äù and we are shooting on October 11th & 12th, 2025. We are currently looking to hire three male actors. For the roles of Athan, Hooded Man, and Rick. If you are interested please send your resume, headshot, and any demo reel to teambeginnings@gmail.com and we will reach out to you for a self tape to help narrow down the process.

The deadline for demo tapes and applications end on October 3rd, 2025. So please get in your application at your earliest convenience.

Synopsis:
Athan celebrates his 21st birthday surrounded by the people he loves the most. Family and
friends cheer for the start of a new phase of Athan‚Äôs life. A new beginning. Until time suddenly
stops. Everyone freezing in place, except for Athan, who knows the memory has ended.
Guided by a Hooded Man, an older and wiser version of himself, Athan must find purpose by
visiting rooms in a seemingly never-ending hallway, each filled with crucial moments of his life
‚Äî learning the role of the people that surround him (and the impact he has on them), dealing
with love in an ever-transforming relationship, and embracing grief from the never-stopping
passage of time.
After impulsively deciding to skip entering the rest of the doors out of agony, Athan will find
how quickly a lifetime goes by ‚Äî but be ready to accept his new chapter behind a final, bright room.

CASTING BREAKDOWN ‚Äì VANCOUVER FILM SCHOOL
Project Title: Beginnings
Project Type: Student Short Film
Union Status: Non-Union
Director: J. D. Estevez
Producer: Raj Heer / Vancouver Film School
Casting Director: Manraj Heer, J. D. Estevez
Audition Dates: Self-tapes due by October 3rd, 2025
Audition Location: Self-tapes only
Call Back Dates: October 4th, 2025
Call Back Location: 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2
Shooting Dates: October 11th ‚Äì 12th, 2025
Shooting Location: Greater Vancouver Area
Rates: Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.
Submission Instructions: Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel
to teambeginnings@gmail.com and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for.

ATHAN / MALE / AGE : 20-25 / ANY ETHNICITY 

Na√Øve and foolish, Athan thinks he knows what he wants from life and what it is to be expected of him ‚Äî learning soon enough that you can never be prepared for what is behind
the next door. Though he is slow to realize the importance of every moment, and too clumsy
to show it, Athan is a deeply caring and empathetic person. He is willing to push everything
out of his way to spend more time with someone he loves. Despite repeatedly stumbling
through the hallway of life, Athan is motivated by a constant search for meaning.

HOODED MAN / MALE / AGE : 50-60 / ANY ETHNICITY
After living as a rebellious young Athan, the Hooded Man walks through the hallway of his life
once again. This time, he reflects on his past, accepting it for what it is, knowing he cannot
change it. Melancholic and somewhat regretful, he guides Athan, emphasizing the
importance of embracing every stage of life, whether joyful or somber. Unlike his younger
self, the Hooded Man moves deliberately through every memory, without hurry, but with
peace. Though seemingly stoic, there is a hint of disturbance behind his expression.

RICK / MALE / AGE : 40-50 / ANY ETHNICITY
Athan‚Äôs father, Rick, is a troubled man. He learned from his family to hide his true feelings and
often relies on bad habits to forget his past mistakes. He was able to distance himself from his
vices when he found a sense of purpose, such as when he married his childhood friend,
Emma. However, it didn't last long. Overwhelmed by regret and fearing that he won‚Äôt make
the most of his life, Rick sees Athan as a chance to start over. He is determined to ensure that
his son won't make the same mistakes he did. However, with his marriage falling apart and
Athan soon becoming independent, Rick can‚Äôt help but start drinking again.

 Look forward to seeing everyone‚Äôs submissions! If you have any questions or concerns please reach me at teambeginnings@gmail.com.

items.text:
CASTING CALL FOR PLAY IN LONDON:

I'm casting four roles (3 female/ 1 male) for a showcase reading of my new play 'The Beat of the Bronzewing' at the Hen & Chickens Theatre in Islington, London on November 12th. 

The Beat of the Bronzewing was longlisted for the Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025 and focuses on three women in remote tropical Australia, desperate to turn their lives around yet paralysed by fear. It explores how their insecurities and the wild landscape magnify their loneliness and isolation, setting them on a course of self-destruction as they increasingly turn on each other. 

Apply via the Google Form link here: ([https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0](https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR5Hu3UGD1qZxdMIWR2d_80GBkptrNYjvmQKWCmydP--a9Hs-hLLyq9GDFqZlA_aem_Tn4v_Jq0QGNGHkakZGOTFw)). 

Know someone who might be interested? Please spread the word!

 

Important info:  

| Rehearsals on November 9th (10am-6pm) and November 12th (2:30-7pm)

| In-person auditions on October 8th (12-5pm) at the Old Red Lion Theatre in Angel, Islington following a selection (let us know if you need an alternative)

items.summary:
CASTING CALL FOR PLAY IN LONDON:

I'm casting four roles (3 female/ 1 male) for a showcase reading of my new play 'The Beat of the Bronzewing' at the Hen & Chickens Theatre in Islington, London on November 12th. 

The Beat of the Bronzewing was longlisted for the Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025 and focuses on three women in remote tropical Australia, desperate to turn their lives around yet paralysed by fear. It explores how their insecurities and the wild landscape magnify their loneliness and isolation, setting them on a course of self-destruction as they increasingly turn on each other. 

Apply via the Google Form link here: ([https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0](https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR5Hu3UGD1qZxdMIWR2d_80GBkptrNYjvmQKWCmydP--a9Hs-hLLyq9GDFqZlA_aem_Tn4v_Jq0QGNGHkakZGOTFw)). 

Know someone who might be interested? Please spread the word!

 

Important info:  

| Rehearsals on November 9th (10am-6pm) and November 12th (2:30-7pm)

| In-person auditions on October 8th (12-5pm) at the Old Red Lion Theatre in Angel, Islington following a selection (let us know if you need an alternative) 

| Volunteer opportunity - all actors will be given ¬£50 pounds for expenses

| Apply via Google Form link here: ([https://t.co/d98EEgkgK0](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fd98EEgkgK0%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAAR6STL3lXt8cdBCGpSYrv5XvpSHW_IA3JoKT1r83vfoq93QMm80Vsj_31_s09Q_aem_cSh3Con8n2nt4AWPGVxuRQ&h=AT3UxWehtfMsSwB5REWXCX3UHOR-IbCtMgXw11AVLk6tzDWjrVusQvMal4tBpcgnFYk6zyQaOjGLupowpQG2C_2Lnir-BGUKBI9MH_CMk-pF1FA-OIIZsoxFFo2bSplp5WYnUXM019O0AA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT3ZSFem3LQLGHpnYQQix_aB1OTC-II_z6ULdAtsi-abLh1hVZ6JVCHBA2u98UrsMqLeuH-VMmJqsPkp102wldtR3ternY9MXCYToG6v5AsMe_3MJvv4-JL2oxzyNfi1_K7uf8f1E10-EvfRY4j_OFAP6nnjb1-iHjbe3u5HTKwR)) - thank you!
items.title: CASTING CALL FOR PLAY IN LONDON:

items.text:
Casting Call

We are looking for actors to make an example scene for the film pitch, with which we are looking for to ask for funding for the feature length low-budget independent film based on a real story, hidden truths and mystic experiences, mixed with fantasy.

The action of the example scene develops, as a guy (20-26 years old) confronts with two young men (26-35 years old), who ask him to give back them money, that a young man borrowed from them for the business, that failed. They are warning him with death and preparing to hit him until death, but accidentally something happens as a hand of help.

It's going be around 3h of filming for one day: 14th of October day time in Croydon, London, next to Waddon station. 

Salary will be ¬£25 for the actor after filming, plus if actor will agree to act in the next, but real film shootings, then agreed compensation of percent of how much the film will earn after distribution.

Acting experience is not necessary, but preferable and being comfortable in front of camera with a wish to act.

Actors:
A young guy with blonde colour hair (20-26 years old)

A young man number 1 with black or brown hair  (26-35 years old)

A young man number 2 with black or brown hair (26-35 years old)

If you are interested, write me:

I am producer and one of the directors of the film. My name: Ieva Kondrataviciute 
Email: ieva.kristina.kondrataviciute@gmail.com
Contact WhatsApp: +44 7548710376

items.text:
**CASTING ROLES OF THE JOKER AND CATWOMAN FOR BATMAN FAN FILM ON YOUTUBE**

Hi my name is Lucas Woolrich. I'm working on a Batman fan film titled Batman Gotham City Sirens. The film will be uploaded onto Youtube. The story for the film would see Batman/Bruce Wayne facing off against Harley Quinn, Catwoman, Poison Ivy, Deathstroke, Black Mask and The Joker.

Here is the list of characters I am looking to cast for the film.

**CATWOMAN**

**THE JOKER **(to be played similar to 2008‚Äôs The Dark Knight‚Äôs version of The Joker)

Filming will be on for one day at the Rachel Almond Dance Academy in Manchester. Filming would last for four hours. Payment would be ¬£20 an hour. Applicants must be 18 years old and over. Also have great improvising skills. Applicants will have to provide their own costume for the role.

Please e-mail me at** superheroes4@outlook.com** if you're interested. Please include resume and headshot. I would appreciate it. Thanks.

topComments.text: I'd have been good as batman. But can definitely play joker!

Summary: Set in the backroom of a dive bar. A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer. Black African, 25-35, Nigerian accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£500 for 20 hours (rehearsals & shoot).

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European, 25-35, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg, powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

You will need professional experience playing roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2filmworks@gmail.com

items.text:
Hey everyone

Currently casting roles for an upcoming dark comedy/horror short film

It is to be filmed in Northern/Central NJ on October 10th & 11th. We have an extremely talented crew and a great script. Here are the two roles we need to fill:

**Matt** (Young male, 20s-30): on the sarcastic side, emotive, physically comedic, able to display fear and be funny simultaneously, slightly over-the-top to play off shock factor/dark comedy bits

**Ron** (Young male, 20s-30): sincere, thoughtful, introspective, innocent. plays it straight to contrast the hyperbole around him

Please DM me if you are interested along with your acting reel. **Must be available both days!**

This is a **volunteer** gig for imdb credit, experience, and the chance to collaborate on a high quality production that will circuit quite a few festivals!

items.text:
We are now casting for our Halloween Party show .

The show will tour into community based venues, Nursing and Residential Homes, Day Centres.

We are seeking self-contained experienced hardworking singer/ performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community.

The Dates

Rehearsals ‚Äì17th and 18th October in London

Playing Dates-20th -31st October-

We work Monday to Friday only.

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced engaging performers with great singing voices,

We are looking for drivers with cars only

Please confirm where you are based in your application.

We offer ¬£700 per week plus fuel on the road .

We are also casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

The show is production style show based on songs from the musicals Mary Poppins, White Christmas, Singing In The Rain, The Wizard Of Oz As well as traditional Christmas songs and carols, comedy routines and festive entertainment for all.

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We perform two 60 minute shows 6 days a week.

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

MUST BE A DRIVER WITH A CAR

Please email details including a singing reel to

info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

Dates

Rehearsals 24th -28th November

Playing dates 1st-23rd December

We are offering 600 .00 per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

**Actors wanted for Dick Whittington, Valley Theatre‚Äôs annual seasonal panto.**

**Audition date and time;**** 7.15pm, Monday 13****th**** October 2025, at Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA**

**Performance dates:**** Sat  17****th**** Jan 2026(afternoon and eve) and Sun  18****th**** Jan 2026 (afternoon only);**

**Rehearsal days;**** Monday 7pm whole cast usually; Thursday eve selected scenes.**

Valley Theatre‚Äôs traditional panto has become legendary in the area. As a community theatre we pride ourselves on keeping the prices family friendly without compromising on the quality. We like to offer a  traditional storyline with well-loved panto routines, popular music, up-to-date and local references, strong on humour.

This is a great opportunity for actors wanting to gain unbeatable stage experience  with a friendly and supportive production team.

Wide range of parts available for the experienced and beginner alike. No prep needed for the audition.

Please note: this is non-paying.

More details [info@valleytheatre.co.uk](mailto:info@valleytheatre.co.uk)

items.text:
Acting & Storytelling Improv Workshop with Arek Ziƒôtek

This is not your usual workshop. This is a rare chance to learn from Arek Ziƒôtek, a Warsaw theater legend who has worked with Keith Johnstone, the father of modern improvisation.

Together, we dive deep into acting, storytelling, and improvisational theater in a way that pushes you to grow, connect, and create.

üëâ Important: This is not an open event. In order to join, prior experience in acting or improv and a confident level of English is required. We‚Äôre keeping this group selective to ensure high quality, intensity, and growth for every participant.

Why join?

‚ú® Learn from one of Poland‚Äôs most respected improv acting teachers.
‚ú® Develop storytelling and performance techniques that translate to stage, film, and beyond.
‚ú® Work in English, one of the very few opportunities in Warsaw to grow artistically in an international setting.
‚ú® Build deep connections with like-minded actors and creators.

Schedule & Pricing

üìÜ Starting: Tuesday, October 7th
‚è∞ 7:00 PM
üìç Location: Atlas Tower - al. jerozolimskie 123a (Warsaw)

üéüÔ∏è Limited Packages:

First 5 applicants: 300 PLN (for full 6-week course)

If more than 10 apply, a second group will be opened, but no guarantees.

üîó Apply now through the link below. Spots will not last, once the first 5 tickets are gone, the price increases.

https://forms.gle/JguLesA9U2uf31BE7

This is your invitation to step into a smaller, more demanding circle of actors who take their craft to the next level.

‚Ä¢CASTING CALL ‚Äì INDEPENDENT FEATURE FILM 
Project Title: Before We Break
Production Type: Independent Feature Film
Shoot Dates: October 10th - 12th.
Location: Denver, CO 
Compensation: $500/day (2 days) + Reel + IMDb Credit

SYNOPSIS:
A week before their high school‚Äôs final closure, five former classmates reunite to bury a time capsule they created years ago. What begins as a nostalgic farewell quickly spirals into a raw confrontation of the truths, betrayals, and dreams that shaped their youth and the adulthood that awaits.
NOW CASTING ‚Äì LEAD & SUPPORTING ROLES:

 LEAD ROLES:

Malik (Male, 18‚Äì23)
Ambitious, witty, and fiercely protective. A natural leader haunted by a decision he made senior year that fractured the group.

Zoey (Female, 18‚Äì24)
Intelligent and emotionally layered. She‚Äôs the planner of the reunion, but secretly fears what might resurface. Carries herself with quiet authority.

Jessie (Female, 19‚Äì25)
Charming and impulsive with a magnetic presence. Struggles with stability and hides vulnerability behind a fearless exterior.

SUPPORTING ROLES:

Cam (Female, 18‚Äì23)
Reserved, observant, and deeply reflective. Once the outsider of the group, she now holds crucial pieces of the past they all want to forget.

Ms. Clarke (Female, 30s‚Äì40s)
A former teacher turned school counselor. Warm, insightful, and a mentor to many, but carries her own regrets about the group‚Äôs final year.

TO SUBMIT:
Email your headshot, resume, and city of residence to:
newdawnfilming@gmail.com 

Subject line: ‚Äú[Your Name] ‚Äì Role Submission for Before We Break‚Äù

CASTING CALL 

Self Tapes Wanted for University of Colorado Denver Senior Thesis Project

In-Person Callbacks in early October

TITLE: *Action! 1987*

PROJECT TYPE: Short Film (Student, Non-Union)

LOCATION: Denver Metro Area

TIMEFRAME: 2 Days of Shooting in late October 

SYNOPSIS: In 1987, a young woman, Luda, leaves a movie theatre with her cinephile boyfriend Julian. They argue about the morality of the action heroes they see on screen. Luda says the so-called ‚Äúgood guys‚Äù are always doing bad things. Julian thinks it‚Äôs more complicated than that.

The next day at work while helping with a children‚Äôs beauty pageant, Luda finds that right and wrong aren‚Äôt always so black and white when the parents of a young girl, Angie, leaves her alone in front of Luda. That night Luda and Julian walk into the movie theatre and she is shocked to see herself up on the silver screen.

COMPENSATION (Non-Union) : Reel, Food, Gas, Undying Appreciation

ROLE: 

Dad (Male, Late 30‚Äôs - Late 40‚Äôs): An stern and demanding pageant Dad with a wandering eye.

Please send your headshot/resume/other materials to [MARLEY.TREMMEL@UCDENVER.EDU](mailto:MARLEY.TREMMEL@UCDENVER.EDU) to receive sides and further instructions for submitting a self-tape. Thank you!

**CASTING CALL**

Til den ambiti√∏se og absurd-komiske kortfilm FLYT DIG, leder vi lige nu efter en r√¶kke skuespillere. 

**LOGLINE**

En konfliktsky ung mand bliver udnyttet af sine venner og ignoreret af sin familie. Da hans rebelske f√¶tter hj√¶lper ham med at flytte, m√• han indse, at frihed ikke bare handler om at bryde ud ‚Äì men om at turde definere sine egne gr√¶nser.

**ADAM **(hovedrolle, omkring 18)
* Ung af udseende
* Stille, meget almindelig, ikke s√¶rlig bem√¶rkelsesv√¶rdig
* har sv√¶rt ved at s√¶tte gr√¶nser

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 1**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 2**

**FAMILIEMEDLEM 3**

**FAMILIE MEDLEM 4**
* BIROLLER, ALLE mellem 40-80 √•r
* ALLE familiemedlemmer har replikker
* K√òN/UDSEENDE er underordnet 

**ROOMIE 1**

**ROOMIE 2**

**ROOMIE 3**
* BIROLLER, DRENGE mellem 17-22
* ALLE roomies har replikker 
* UDSEENDE er underordnet

Optagelserne kommer til at ligge i Aarhus, omkring datoerne 14-15-16 oktober. Da dette er i samarbejde med Potemkin, Den Jyske Filmskole, er rollerne ul√∏nnet.

Hvis man er interesseret i en/flere af rollerne, bedes man sende en mail p√• sara774g@gmail.som med alder og eventuel erfaring/showreel.

Vi gl√¶der os til at h√∏re fra jer!

Vh 

Sara Riahi, Freya Carlsen & Sylvester Byder

items.text:
Heyyy! I‚Äôm Anne Musisi and I‚Äôm an actor, director, and career development coach with a mission to help creatives and actors thrive. Drawing on decades of experience in global theatre, screen, and coaching, I‚Äôve created a wellbeing tool designed specifically for actors and creatives. My mission is to help you overcome self-doubt, reconnect with your creative core, and build a sustainable, fulfilling career.

It is also a tool that can be used by therapists, coaches and facilitators to spark deeper conversations and even provide a thematic structure for your workshops. 

My work merges creative practice with personal growth and career strategy. This tool is the practical embodiment of my belief: that when creatives nurture their inner life, their art and profession flourish too.

If you or anyone are interested in learning more, do feel free to DM. I‚Äôd love to chat more.
https://www.annemusisi.com

**Autumn greetings to all our actors from Estonia and beyond!** üçÇüçÅ

All-level Meisner workshop taking place in Tallinn soon!

Join us, November 15‚Äì16th, for a two-day workshop with actor coach Dominic Kelly.

Whether you‚Äôre just starting out or looking to deepen your practice, this course offers a focused exploration of Sanford Meisner‚Äôs core exercises‚Äîhelping you access and express your most truthful impulses in response to your partner‚Äôs behavior.

You‚Äôll learn to:
 ‚ú® access your most truthful impulses
 ‚ú® connect deeply with your partner
 ‚ú® strengthen your instincts & emotional expression
 ‚ú® create freedom to be fully present, on stage and in life

This workshop is both a training ground and a safe space to challenge yourself, explore truth in performance, and deepen your connection to others and the imaginary world of a scene.

For our alumni, we have the option to work on a short, self-chosen scene on the second day (Let us know by email in advance if you would like to do this)

  üóì When: **15‚Äì16 November 2025 | 10:00‚Äì16:00**
  üìç Where: **Tallinn, Old Town**
  üë• For: Actors, performers, directors, writers, coaches‚Äîanyone curious about living & working more truthfully

Spots are limited, book yours in here:

Casting for: Queer actresses, episodic series leads types, early 20's.

Holding open auditions for several new queer episodic series we are working on, looking for actresses who can play women who are just about to meet/are at the start of same-sex dating and relationships.

Open ethnicity, early 20's look, attractive, in shape. Non-union. Paid (TBD). Actors do not actually need to be queer, just be able to play the role.

Auditions are Friday, Saturday, Sunday, October 10th, 11th, 12th in East Vancouver studio. You will perform a short set of sides and then do a monologue of your choice.

Shooting will be in Winter 2025/2026.

If interested, please email castingproject604@gmail.comNOSPAM (remove 'NOSPAM') with your photos, resume with a cover letter about your experience or any training you have had and your availability for the three dates.

Shortlisted talent will be asked to audition.

Thank you for your attention.

CASTING/HIRING: Superhero Performers!

Dream Party Productions is looking for Superhero Performers for Children events across the Greater Vancouver Area. 

REQUIREMENTS:
* Must have experience working with children
* MUST own a vehicle
* Must be willing to obtain a criminal record check
* Must be 18 years or older
* Acting/Musical Theatre experience preferred but not required

Please email us at Dreampartyproductions@outlook.com with a short introduction, relevant experience, and a front-facing photo! Please feel free to reach out if you have any questions. We look forward to hearing from you. ü§©üôåü¶∏

Find all of our characters here: https://dreampartyproductions.com/characters

Find us on instagram: @dreampartyproductions

CASTING CALL 

Seeking actors for a Boston University Capstone Thesis (Prod3) Film. 

looking for

Hispanic/Latine women 15-55 (two different roles)

Screen Acting ‚Ä¢ SAG Aftra set ‚Ä¢ IMDB Credit ‚Ä¢ Minimal travel costs (parking or public transport) & Food compensated 

Native Spanish speaking ‚Ä¢ Shooting in Boston area 

Logline: 17-year-old Esme, faced with fear and uncertainty, must shield her 8-year-old baby brother, Juan, from the truth when humanity takes part in separating her family. 

Please reach out to *sofiagi@bu.edu* for sides for self tapes and any other additional information.

**PROJECT NAME**: *DESTINATION OSHAWA*

**PROJECT TYPE:** *WEBSERIES - COMEDY*

**STATUS:*** NON-UNION*

**COMPENSATION**: DAILY HONORARIUM *CAD $2*00/Day- please note cast and crew for this project are working on an equity daily honorarium. 

**SYPNOPSIS**:  [Hannah is suddenly appointed director of the Oshawa Tourism Board due to her boss‚Äôs unexpected passing. She is tasked with getting Oshawa off the ‚ÄúWorst Cities in Canada‚Äù list by the end of the year. With almost no resources or time, it‚Äôs up to Hannah to inspire her chaotic team and fulfill her promise of putting Oshawa on the map (in a good way).](https://www.canva.com/design/DAGYFsS-yL4/PVPHv0y53k9FrFZNwakJOg/view?utm_content=DAGYFsS-yL4&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link&utm_source=editor#page-1)

***SHOOTING LOCATIONS:**** Richmond Hill + Oshawa*

***PRODUCTION DATES: ****October 17-24 (individual shoot dates TBD)*

***CASTING SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS: ***

*To request an audition and sides, please send headshots, reels and any info to **[casting@combobravo.com](mailto:casting@combobravo.com)** with the character name in the subject line. ****ie - BELLA RANDAZZO - ASHLEY***

***CHARACTER****:  *Ashley
***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****33*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****Brown Hair, sweet face. *Neat, tidy, formal wear in the office. Patagonia vests, khakis on field trips. *Think Gabe Lewis (The Office)*

***About Character:**** *Liaison to City Council, Ashley has always been passionate about efficient government bureaucracy to a fault. His do-gooder nature has always made him generally unlikeable by his peers and higher ups. In high school he was the first class president to be impeached by faculty, and he was the first student to ever be assassinated at model UN. Despite that he never lost his innocence, and kept on pursuing his dream of joining the Canadian government. He loves his job as Council Liaison and self-appointed apprentice to Bill Tuft. He planned his life out long ago and it is going exactly according to plan, until he met Hannah. He fell in love with her as soon as she started working as Bill‚Äôs assistant, and when he was drafted to join the Tourism Task Force, he dedicated himself to making sure her goals are achieved. She is truly the one person in his life that throws his rational, ordered nature into disarray. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Sarah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****20*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****5‚Äô2, petite, unassuming student. *

***About Character:**** *Newest intern at Oshawa City Hall. Was reassigned to the Tourism Task Force. In a constant state of panic. She wants to please everyone all the time but is constantly second guessing herself. She is very introverted unless she‚Äôs having one of her stress- induced, fugue-state outbursts. Fearing for the other students safety, Sarah was sent to Oshawa City Hall by her guidance counsellor as they felt a ‚Äúnoncompetitive and ineffectual environment‚Äù would be a good change of pace for her. The task force team is unfazed by her outbursts and for the first time Sarah feels as though she‚Äôs found her pack. Their acceptance helps Sarah gain confidence and start standing up for herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Deborah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****60*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ***Stocky, older, greying a bit but also dyes her hair. Business casual, but stopped updating her wardrobe in the 90s.

***About Character:**** *Has been working at City Hall since gaining her business degree from Durham College. She stopped caring about her job around the time everything moved online and although she would never admit it, feels a bit archaic and forgotten. She‚Äôs annoyed she was moved onto Hannah‚Äôs task force as she doesn't want to waste her time learning new skills for a project that seems destined to fail. She‚Äôs not bitter, she's just seen it all before. Eventually, Deborah is motivated after some emotional vulnerability from Hannah, perhaps remembering a younger version of herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Bill Tuft

***Role Type****: *Reoccuring

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****51*

***Episode: ****1-2, 4*

***Appearance: ***Tall, athletic, greying. Suit with no tie kind of guy, but always a flashy pocket square. On fridays and weekends he wears his golf attire. Think Richard Greenwood, (Workin‚Äô Moms)

***About Character:**** *Former real estate agent, but has been the Ward 5 City Councillor 15 years running. Bill is considered a ‚ÄúGreybeard‚Äù or municipal government. He‚Äôs been at it for a long time and knows all the ins and outs. He‚Äôs incredibly popular, not just because of his extreme charisma, but also his moral flexibility when it comes allowing a ‚Äúhealthy dose‚Äù of political corruption. He likes ambitious people that know what they want, and won‚Äôt let moral or legal guidelines stifle their vision. He saw a lot of potential in Hannah when she started as his assistant. When Hannah hit her rock bottom, it was his idea to give her a leave of absence, as he felt a sense of responsibility for her. He‚Äôs given Hannah six months to show what she‚Äôs made of. If it works, he looks like a genius. If she fails, it‚Äôs not much money, his conscience is clear and in the meantime he can use the Task Force to his own personal and financial benefit when the opportunity arises.

***CHARACTER****:  *Nick

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***28

***Episode: ****2*

***Appearance: ***White, thin and kind of scrawny. Slim shady like. Oshawa generals jersey. Knock off designer hat and shoes. Chain. Energetic, passionate, feels his emotions and is confident in them, which can make him a prima donna. The fashion of J Roc, the delivery of Western U frat bro, and the sincerity of a ‚Äúcool‚Äù youth pastor, 

***About Character:**** *After getting his Bachelors from Western, Nick gave up on higher education to pursue his dream of becoming a hip hop legend. He moved back in with his mom and  new husband, Bill Tuft, at his mansion. That was 5 years ago. When Bill learns that the Task Force is putting together a tourism music video, he sees this as an opportunity to include Nick in order to write off past studio personal expenses. Nick joins forces with Jam Easy in making a great song, and wins his step-dad‚Äôs respect of his art. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Gord ‚ÄúConspiracy Guy‚Äù 

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***39

***Episode: ****2,4*

***Appearance: ***White, grisled beard, weary eyes, military surplus gear, phone mounted on a chest rig. Husky, but strong with a surprising range of movement, like a former soldier who‚Äôs stopped training.

***About Character:**** *Gord is a conspiracy-minded ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù who proudly identifies as a sovereign citizen.  He spends his days moderating threads on Truth Social, and uploading videos of his ‚Äúauditing‚Äù police and other government workers to his pro-freedom channel. He‚Äôs paranoid, he‚Äôs ready for a fight, but when you get down to it he‚Äôs very thin-skinned. He comes across the Oshawa Tourism Task Force filming different Oshawa landmarks, he confronts them for ‚Äúinvading his privacy‚Äù and casts paranoid suspicions about their true intent. When Ashley arrives with his ‚Äùspy drone‚Äù, Gord takes it as a moment of bittersweet triumph: the government really is after him, and his ‚Äútruth warrior‚Äù life wasn‚Äôt wasted.

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin Impersonator #1

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Middle aged man who is neither physically matching nor dressed for the part of Samuel.

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but quickly fails when he not only cannot remember his line - ‚ÄúOshawa‚Äù, but is legally required to let the task force know he‚Äôs not allowed within a certain distance of any children at the celebration.  

***CHARACTER****:  *Samuel McLaughlin, R.S

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***45

***Episode: ***3

***Appearance: ***Teddy Roosevelt aesthetic. Neatly trimmed, but bushy moustache. Balding, broad shoulders, stern, sharp eyes. (Think the real Samuel McLaughlin)

***About Character:**** *Samuel shows up at the office to audition as an R.S. McLaughlin impersonator for the upcoming civic holiday, but he insists he is not an actor at all and seems to believe he‚Äôs the real Samuel McLaughlin. Once hired, Samuel lingers in the office and gradually assumes control of the task force by exploiting weaknesses in Hannah‚Äôs communication with her team.

***CHARACTER****:  *Willie

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***66

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thinning white/grey uncombed hair, beer belly, red face, weathered skin. Slow moving and a slow vocal pace. He never wants to finish his sentence because it‚Äôll give the listener a chance to leave. Vintage, worn rumpled clothes. A hat that looks like he‚Äôs been wearing it for 50 years. 

***About Character:**** *A local Oshawa ‚ÄúShwallywood legend‚Äù that has had hundreds of TV and Movie productions use his driveway. A lonely drinker and compulsive liar, a bad one at that, When Jam Easy needs to stall on his Hollywood Tour, he brings his group to Willie, who shares ‚ÄúForrest Gumpian‚Äù stories of how he changed movie history, and bragging about absurdly close friendships with movie stars. Obviously no one believes him, which makes him sad. He just just excited to have someone to talk to.

***CHARACTER****:*  Clara ‚ÄúNewswoman‚Äù

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***40‚Äôs

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Mid-40s, attractive but not delicate, with a confident, professional presence. Simple hair, and a face showing experience rather than youth. Blazer, smart blouse, tailored slacks. Carries a small microphone with the channel logo, Minimal jewelry. 

***About Character: ***Field reporter for a Durham Region news channel. Polished but practical, someone who can run to a chaotic scene without ruining her outfit. Clara is on-site at the Oshawa tourism task force‚Äôs Hollywood Tour location, where a body has been discovered. She delivers the story with gravity despite the absurdity of the situation. 

***CHARACTER****:* Chris

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Medium build, white, dark hair. Nerdy, glasses, thrifted clothes or ones he picked up at Costco

***About Character: ***full-time software engineer but would rather talk about his many hobbies and interests like the golden age of cinema, Napoleon, his tropical fish tank, pickleball league and making his girlfriend Julia happy. Chris saw an online ad for the Shwallywood Tour and immediately booked it as he had been looking for a way to propose to his girlfriend, Julia, for months. On the day of, Chris does not immediately react when the tour seems to be taking much longer than anticipated to get to Parkwood as he is a calm and patient person. He only becomes upset when he sees his girlfriend Julia is disappointed in the lackluster activities of the day.

***CHARACTER****:*  Julia

***Role Type****: *OCP

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ***29

***Episode: ***4

***Appearance: ***Thin frame, blonde or dark brown hair, A little nerdy, soft goth. 

***About Character: ***Works as a dental assistant. She realized she had a passion for teeth when she did a work placement as a mortician in high school. Julia has been taken on the Shwallywood tour by Chris, to celebrate their anniversary. She initially had very little interest, but Chris insisted on bringing her because she‚Äôs a movie buff. The tour is off to a rough start, but as the tour progresses, Julia‚Äôs eccentric side emerges. She enjoys the macabre and is intrigued by some of the stranger stops, though her frustration continues as Chris struggles to give an honest take on the experience.

items.text:
**Casting for: East Asian actors, all types, all ages**

Holding open auditions for Asian actors, men and women, for a number of Asian film and episodic projects (action, thriller, drama, rom-com) we are working on.

East Asian ethnicity, looking for early 20's look (for group 1) and all ages (for group 2). Non-union. Payment status depends on the project.

Auditions are Friday, Saturday, Sunday, October 10th, 11th, 12th in East Vancouver studio. You will perform a short set of sides and then do a monologue of your choice.

Shooting will be throughout Fall and Winter 2025/2026.

If interested, please email castingproject604@gmail.comNOSPAM (remove 'NOSPAM') with your photos, resume with a cover letter about your experience or any training you have had and your availability for the three dates.

Shortlisted talent will be asked to audition.

Thank you for your attention.

items.text:
**Casting for: Korean Kpop Idol types, early 20's.**

Holding open auditions for several projects we are working on, looking for actors and actresses who can play  Korean Kpop singers and idols. This is not a music project, this is a short film/webseries project, thus looking for acting talent.

Asian ethnicity, early 20's look, attractive, in shape. You do not need to be Korean and you do not need to know how to sing (but if you can, that is a bonus). Non-union. Paid (TBD).

Auditions are Friday, Saturday, Sunday, October 10th, 11th, 12th in East Vancouver studio. You will perform a short set of sides and then do a monologue of your choice.

Shooting will be in Winter 2026.

If interested, please email castingproject604@gmail.comNOSPAM (remove 'NOSPAM') with your photos, resume with a cover letter about your experience or any training you have had and your availability for the three dates.

Shortlisted talent will be asked to audition.

Thank you for your attention.

Looking for five diverse talents for a two-day photography project in showcasing community services and programs. Professional photo shoot requiring natural, authentic interactions representing local residents.

Desired Attributes:

  ‚Ä¢ Non-union

  ‚Ä¢ Mixed ages and ethnicities to represent community diversity

  ‚Ä¢ Senior (Age 65+)

  ‚Ä¢ Young students (Age 18-22)

  ‚Ä¢ Young professionals (Age 30-40)

  ‚Ä¢ Comfortable with professional photography environment

  ‚Ä¢ Natural, approachable appearance

Usage:
